<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?>

<chapter xml:id="ch-first-order-autonomous" xmlns:xi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XInclude">
  <title>First Order Autonomous ODEs and Applications</title>

  <introduction>
    <p>
      In this chapter we study first order autonomous ODEs, which are equations where the rate of change
      depends only on the current state, not explicitly on time. We explore three important
      applications: resistive forces, population modelling, and the stability of equilibrium solutions.
    </p>
  </introduction>

  <xi:include href="./sections/sec-2-1.ptx" />
  <xi:include href="./sections/sec-2-2.ptx" />
  

</chapter>